                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/854: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-23T16:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1923—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>419. Contents of your 290, October 20, 1 p.m. to London, repeated to this
                    Embassy, brought to the attention of the Foreign Office today which gives verbal
                    assurances pending written reply that American citizens in Tangier will continue
                    to enjoy rights and privileges provided for in the Act of Algeciras.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office informs me that French Government proposes to suggest to
                    signatories of the Act of Algeciras that diplomatic agencies at Tangier be
                    abolished and that consuls general stationed at Rabat be substituted. The
                    signatory powers will besides maintain consuls at Tangier who will represent
                    their respective governments in the internationalized local municipal
                    administration.</p>
                <p>The rest of the French program would appear to coincide with the statements
                    contained in telegram no. 417, October 1, 6 p.m. to the Department from London
                    Embassy.</p>
                <p>Repeated to London and Madrid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
